What Did
Scanned my local network using Nessus Essentials installed on Kali Linux.
Targeted the subnet 172.16.2.0/24 using a Basic Network Scan.
Objective was to find actual vulnerabilities and understand how Nessus reports them.

Tools Used
Nessus Essentials

Kali Linux

Browser (https://localhost:8834 for Nessus dashboard)

Steps Followed
Installed Nessus using .deb file and started service

Accessed dashboard and set up a new scan on 172.16.2.0/24

Waited for the scan to complete (around 45 min)

Checked which hosts were found and filtered for only critical vulnerabilities
                      
